Sunday Nwakanma, Umuahia The Abia State Governor, Dr Okezie Ikpeazu, has directed the sacking of the General Manager of Abia State Environmental Sanitation Agency, Mr Okechukwu Apugo, over poor sanitation situation in Umuahia. According to a statement by the Commissioner for Information, Chief JohnÂ  Kalu, the governor gave the directive after he saw heaps of refuse along the road while on project tour of the state. Ikpeazu directed the Secretary to the State Government, Chris Ezem, to take over the sanitation in Umuahia with the immediate -past Commissioner for Environment and now commissioner nominee, Dr Aham Uko, assisting him. Meanwhile Ikpeazu said he would complete all ongoing projects in the state without compromising on quality. He spoke after the project tour, pointing out that the funds for the projects were ready. Ikpeazu said he had established Operation Zero Portholes in Aba and Umuahia to ensure that the roads in the two metropolises were rehabilitated. Copyright PUNCH.
